52/**
53* The following code is the 'old' code by Sean Owen based on the Java upstream project.
54* It looks for a white rectangle, then cuts the corners until it hits a black pixel, which
55* results in 4 corner points. Then it determines the dimension by counting transitions
56* between the upper and right corners and samples the grid.
57* This code has several limitations compared to the new code below but has one advantage:
58* it works on high resolution scans with noisy/rippled black/white-edges and potentially
59* on partly occluded locator patterns (the surrounding border of modules/pixels). It is
60* therefore kept as a fall-back.
61*/
62
63/**
64* Simply encapsulates two points and a number of transitions between them.
65*/
66struct ResultPointsAndTransitions
67{
68 const ResultPoint* from;
69 const ResultPoint* to;
70 int transitions;
71};
72
73/**
74* Counts the number of black/white transitions between two points, using something like Bresenham's algorithm.
75*/
76static ResultPointsAndTransitions TransitionsBetween(const BitMatrix& image, const ResultPoint& from,
77 const ResultPoint& to)
78{
79 // See QR Code Detector, sizeOfBlackWhiteBlackRun()
80 int fromX = static_cast<int>(from.x());
81 int fromY = static_cast<int>(from.y());
82 int toX = static_cast<int>(to.x());
83 int toY = static_cast<int>(to.y());
84 bool steep = std::abs(toY - fromY) > std::abs(toX - fromX);
85 if (steep) {
86 std::swap(fromX, fromY);
87 std::swap(toX, toY);
88 }
89
90 int dx = std::abs(toX - fromX);
91 int dy = std::abs(toY - fromY);
92 int error = -dx / 2;
93 int ystep = fromY < toY ? 1 : -1;
94 int xstep = fromX < toX ? 1 : -1;
95 int transitions = 0;
96 bool inBlack = image.get(steep ? fromY : fromX, steep ? fromX : fromY);
97 for (int x = fromX, y = fromY; x != toX; x += xstep) {
98 bool isBlack = image.get(steep ? y : x, steep ? x : y);
99 if (isBlack != inBlack) {
100 transitions++;
101 inBlack = isBlack;
102 }
103 error += dy;
104 if (error > 0) {
105 if (y == toY) {
106 break;
107 }
108 y += ystep;
109 error -= dx;
110 }
111 }
112 return ResultPointsAndTransitions{ &from, &to, transitions };
113}
114
115inline static bool IsValidPoint(const ResultPoint& p, int imgWidth, int imgHeight)
116{
117 return p.x() >= 0 && p.x() < imgWidth && p.y() > 0 && p.y() < imgHeight;
118}
119
120inline static float RoundToNearest(float x)
121{
122 return std::round(x);
123}
124
125/**
126* Calculates the position of the white top right module using the output of the rectangle detector
127* for a rectangular matrix
128*/
129static bool CorrectTopRightRectangular(const BitMatrix& image, const ResultPoint& bottomLeft,
130 const ResultPoint& bottomRight, const ResultPoint& topLeft,
131 const ResultPoint& topRight, int dimensionTop, int dimensionRight,
132 ResultPoint& result)
133{
134 float corr = RoundToNearest(distance(bottomLeft, bottomRight)) / static_cast<float>(dimensionTop);
135 float norm = RoundToNearest(distance(topLeft, topRight));
136 float cos = (topRight.x() - topLeft.x()) / norm;
137 float sin = (topRight.y() - topLeft.y()) / norm;
138
139 ResultPoint c1(topRight.x() + corr*cos, topRight.y() + corr*sin);
140
141 corr = RoundToNearest(distance(bottomLeft, topLeft)) / (float)dimensionRight;
142 norm = RoundToNearest(distance(bottomRight, topRight));
143 cos = (topRight.x() - bottomRight.x()) / norm;
144 sin = (topRight.y() - bottomRight.y()) / norm;
145
146 ResultPoint c2(topRight.x() + corr*cos, topRight.y() + corr*sin);
147
148 if (!IsValidPoint(c1, image.width(), image.height())) {
149 if (IsValidPoint(c2, image.width(), image.height())) {
150 result = c2;
151 return true;
152 }
153 return false;
154 }
155 if (!IsValidPoint(c2, image.width(), image.height())) {
156 result = c1;
157 return true;
158 }
159
160 int l1 = std::abs(dimensionTop - TransitionsBetween(image, topLeft, c1).transitions) +
161 std::abs(dimensionRight - TransitionsBetween(image, bottomRight, c1).transitions);
162 int l2 = std::abs(dimensionTop - TransitionsBetween(image, topLeft, c2).transitions) +
163 std::abs(dimensionRight - TransitionsBetween(image, bottomRight, c2).transitions);
164
165 result = l1 <= l2 ? c1 : c2;
166 return true;
167}
168
169/**
170* Calculates the position of the white top right module using the output of the rectangle detector
171* for a square matrix
172*/
173static ResultPoint CorrectTopRight(const BitMatrix& image, const ResultPoint& bottomLeft, const ResultPoint& bottomRight,
174 const ResultPoint& topLeft, const ResultPoint& topRight, int dimension)
175{
176 float corr = RoundToNearest(distance(bottomLeft, bottomRight)) / (float)dimension;
177 float norm = RoundToNearest(distance(topLeft, topRight));
178 float cos = (topRight.x() - topLeft.x()) / norm;
179 float sin = (topRight.y() - topLeft.y()) / norm;
180
181 ResultPoint c1(topRight.x() + corr * cos, topRight.y() + corr * sin);
182
183 corr = RoundToNearest(distance(bottomLeft, topLeft)) / (float)dimension;
184 norm = RoundToNearest(distance(bottomRight, topRight));
185 cos = (topRight.x() - bottomRight.x()) / norm;
186 sin = (topRight.y() - bottomRight.y()) / norm;
187
188 ResultPoint c2(topRight.x() + corr * cos, topRight.y() + corr * sin);
189
190 if (!IsValidPoint(c1, image.width(), image.height())) {
191 if (!IsValidPoint(c2, image.width(), image.height()))
192 return topRight;
193 return c2;
194 }
195 if (!IsValidPoint(c2, image.width(), image.height()))
196 return c1;
197
198 int l1 = std::abs(TransitionsBetween(image, topLeft, c1).transitions -
199 TransitionsBetween(image, bottomRight, c1).transitions);
200 int l2 = std::abs(TransitionsBetween(image, topLeft, c2).transitions -
201 TransitionsBetween(image, bottomRight, c2).transitions);
202 return l1 <= l2 ? c1 : c2;
203}
204
205static DetectorResult SampleGrid(const BitMatrix& image, const ResultPoint& topLeft, const ResultPoint& bottomLeft,
206 const ResultPoint& bottomRight, const ResultPoint& topRight, int width, int height)
207{
208 return SampleGrid(image, width, height,
209 {Rectangle(width, height, 0.5), {topLeft, topRight, bottomRight, bottomLeft}});
210}

212/**
213* Returns the z component of the cross product between vectors BC and BA.
214*/
215static float CrossProductZ(const ResultPoint& a, const ResultPoint& b, const ResultPoint& c)
216{
217 return (c.x() - b.x())*(a.y() - b.y()) - (c.y() - b.y())*(a.x() - b.x());
218}
219
220/**
221* Orders an array of three ResultPoints in an order [A,B,C] such that AB is less than AC
222* and BC is less than AC, and the angle between BC and BA is less than 180 degrees.
223*
224* @param patterns array of three {@code ResultPoint} to order
225*/
226static void OrderByBestPatterns(const ResultPoint*& p0, const ResultPoint*& p1, const ResultPoint*& p2)
227{
228 // Find distances between pattern centers
229 float zeroOneDistance = distance(*p0, *p1);
230 float oneTwoDistance = distance(*p1, *p2);
231 float zeroTwoDistance = distance(*p0, *p2);
232
233 const ResultPoint* pointA;
234 const ResultPoint* pointB;
235 const ResultPoint* pointC;
236 // Assume one closest to other two is B; A and C will just be guesses at first
237 if (oneTwoDistance >= zeroOneDistance && oneTwoDistance >= zeroTwoDistance) {
238 pointB = p0;
239 pointA = p1;
240 pointC = p2;
241 }
242 else if (zeroTwoDistance >= oneTwoDistance && zeroTwoDistance >= zeroOneDistance) {
243 pointB = p1;
244 pointA = p0;
245 pointC = p2;
246 }
247 else {
248 pointB = p2;
249 pointA = p0;
250 pointC = p1;
251 }
252
253 // Use cross product to figure out whether A and C are correct or flipped.
254 // This asks whether BC x BA has a positive z component, which is the arrangement
255 // we want for A, B, C. If it's negative, then we've got it flipped around and
256 // should swap A and C.
257 if (CrossProductZ(*pointA, *pointB, *pointC) < 0.0f) {
258 std::swap(pointA, pointC);
259 }
260
261 p0 = pointA;
262 p1 = pointB;
263 p2 = pointC;
264}
265
266static DetectorResult DetectOld(const BitMatrix& image)
267{
268 ResultPoint pointA, pointB, pointC, pointD;
269 if (!WhiteRectDetector::Detect(image, pointA, pointB, pointC, pointD)) {
270 return {};
271 }
272
273 // Point A and D are across the diagonal from one another,
274 // as are B and C. Figure out which are the solid black lines
275 // by counting transitions
276 std::array<ResultPointsAndTransitions, 4> transitions = {
277 TransitionsBetween(image, pointA, pointB),
278 TransitionsBetween(image, pointA, pointC),
279 TransitionsBetween(image, pointB, pointD),
280 TransitionsBetween(image, pointC, pointD),
281 };
282 std::sort(transitions.begin(), transitions.end(),
283 [](const ResultPointsAndTransitions& a, const ResultPointsAndTransitions& b) {
284 return a.transitions < b.transitions;
285 });
286
287 // Sort by number of transitions. First two will be the two solid sides; last two
288 // will be the two alternating black/white sides
289 const auto& lSideOne = transitions[0];
290 const auto& lSideTwo = transitions[1];
291
292 // Figure out which point is their intersection by tallying up the number of times we see the
293 // endpoints in the four endpoints. One will show up twice.
294 std::map<const ResultPoint*, int> pointCount;
295 pointCount[lSideOne.from] += 1;
296 pointCount[lSideOne.to] += 1;
297 pointCount[lSideTwo.from] += 1;
298 pointCount[lSideTwo.to] += 1;
299
300 const ResultPoint* bottomRight = nullptr;
301 const ResultPoint* bottomLeft = nullptr;
302 const ResultPoint* topLeft = nullptr;
303 for (const auto& entry : pointCount) {
304 if (entry.second == 2) {
305 bottomLeft = entry.first; // this is definitely the bottom left, then -- end of two L sides
306 }
307 else {
308 // Otherwise it's either top left or bottom right -- just assign the two arbitrarily now
309 if (bottomRight == nullptr) {
310 bottomRight = entry.first;
311 }
312 else {
313 topLeft = entry.first;
314 }
315 }
316 }
317
318 if (bottomRight == nullptr || bottomLeft == nullptr || topLeft == nullptr) {
319 return {};
320 }
321
322 // Bottom left is correct but top left and bottom right might be switched
323 // Use the dot product trick to sort them out
324 OrderByBestPatterns(bottomRight, bottomLeft, topLeft);
325
326 // Which point didn't we find in relation to the "L" sides? that's the top right corner
327 const ResultPoint* topRight;
328 if (pointCount.find(&pointA) == pointCount.end()) {
329 topRight = &pointA;
330 }
331 else if (pointCount.find(&pointB) == pointCount.end()) {
332 topRight = &pointB;
333 }
334 else if (pointCount.find(&pointC) == pointCount.end()) {
335 topRight = &pointC;
336 }
337 else {
338 topRight = &pointD;
339 }
340
341 // Next determine the dimension by tracing along the top or right side and counting black/white
342 // transitions. Since we start inside a black module, we should see a number of transitions
343 // equal to 1 less than the code dimension. Well, actually 2 less, because we are going to
344 // end on a black module:
345
346 // The top right point is actually the corner of a module, which is one of the two black modules
347 // adjacent to the white module at the top right. Tracing to that corner from either the top left
348 // or bottom right should work here.
349
350 int dimensionTop = TransitionsBetween(image, *topLeft, *topRight).transitions;
351 int dimensionRight = TransitionsBetween(image, *bottomRight, *topRight).transitions;
352
353 if ((dimensionTop & 0x01) == 1) {
354 // it can't be odd, so, round... up?
355 dimensionTop++;
356 }
357 dimensionTop += 2;
358
359 if ((dimensionRight & 0x01) == 1) {
360 // it can't be odd, so, round... up?
361 dimensionRight++;
362 }
363 dimensionRight += 2;
364
365 if (dimensionTop < 10 || dimensionTop > 144 || dimensionRight < 8 || dimensionRight > 144 )
366 return {};
367
368 ResultPoint correctedTopRight;
369
370 // Rectanguar symbols are 6x16, 6x28, 10x24, 10x32, 14x32, or 14x44. If one dimension is more
371 // than twice the other, it's certainly rectangular, but to cut a bit more slack we accept it as
372 // rectangular if the bigger side is at least 7/4 times the other:
373 if (4 * dimensionTop >= 7 * dimensionRight || 4 * dimensionRight >= 7 * dimensionTop) {
374 // The matrix is rectangular
375
376 if (!CorrectTopRightRectangular(image, *bottomLeft, *bottomRight, *topLeft, *topRight, dimensionTop,
377 dimensionRight, correctedTopRight)) {
378 correctedTopRight = *topRight;
379 }
380
381 dimensionTop = TransitionsBetween(image, *topLeft, correctedTopRight).transitions;
382 dimensionRight = TransitionsBetween(image, *bottomRight, correctedTopRight).transitions;
383
384 if ((dimensionTop & 0x01) == 1) {
385 // it can't be odd, so, round... up?
386 dimensionTop++;
387 }
388
389 if ((dimensionRight & 0x01) == 1) {
390 // it can't be odd, so, round... up?
391 dimensionRight++;
392 }
393 }
394 else {
395 // The matrix is square
396
397 int dimension = std::min(dimensionRight, dimensionTop);
398 // correct top right point to match the white module
399 correctedTopRight = CorrectTopRight(image, *bottomLeft, *bottomRight, *topLeft, *topRight, dimension);
400
401 // Redetermine the dimension using the corrected top right point
402 int dimensionCorrected = std::max(TransitionsBetween(image, *topLeft, correctedTopRight).transitions,
403 TransitionsBetween(image, *bottomRight, correctedTopRight).transitions);
404 dimensionCorrected++;
405 if ((dimensionCorrected & 0x01) == 1) {
406 dimensionCorrected++;
407 }
408
409 dimensionTop = dimensionRight = dimension;
410 }
411
412 return SampleGrid(image, *topLeft, *bottomLeft, *bottomRight, correctedTopRight, dimensionTop, dimensionRight);
413}
414
415/**
416* The following code is the 'new' one implemented by Axel Waggershauser and is working completely different.
417* It is performing something like a (back) trace search along edges through the bit matrix, first looking for
418* the 'L'-pattern, then tracing the black/white borders at the top/right. Advantages over the old code are:
419* * works with lower resolution scans (around 2 pixel per module), due to sub-pixel precision grid placement
420* * works with real-world codes that have just one module wide quite-zone (which is perfectly in spec)
421*/
422
423class RegressionLine
424{
425 std::vector<PointI> _points;
426 PointF _directionInward;
427 double a = NAN, b = NAN, c = NAN;
428
429 friend PointF intersect(const RegressionLine& l1, const RegressionLine& l2);
430
431 bool evaluate(const std::vector<PointI>& ps)
432 {
433 auto mean = std::accumulate(ps.begin(), ps.end(), PointF()) / ps.size();
434 double sumXX = 0, sumYY = 0, sumXY = 0;
435 for (auto& p : ps) {
436 sumXX += (p.x - mean.x) * (p.x - mean.x);
437 sumYY += (p.y - mean.y) * (p.y - mean.y);
438 sumXY += (p.x - mean.x) * (p.y - mean.y);
439 }
440 if (sumYY >= sumXX) {
441 a = +sumYY / std::sqrt(sumYY * sumYY + sumXY * sumXY);
442 b = -sumXY / std::sqrt(sumYY * sumYY + sumXY * sumXY);
443 } else {
444 a = +sumXY / std::sqrt(sumXX * sumXX + sumXY * sumXY);
445 b = -sumXX / std::sqrt(sumXX * sumXX + sumXY * sumXY);
446 }
447 if (_directionInward * normal() < 0) {
448 a = -a;
449 b = -b;
450 }
451 c = normal() * mean; // (a*mean.x + b*mean.y);
452 return _directionInward * normal() > 0.5; // angle between original and new direction is at most 60 degree
453 }
454
455 template <typename Container, typename Filter>
456 static double average(const Container& c, Filter f)
457 {
458 double sum = 0;
459 int num = 0;
460 for (const auto& v : c)
461 if (f(v)) {
462 sum += v;
463 ++num;
464 }
465 return sum / num;
466 }
467
468public:
469 const std::vector<PointI>& points() const { return _points; }
470 int length() const { return _points.size() >= 2 ? int(distance(_points.front(), _points.back())) : 0; }
471 bool isValid() const { return !std::isnan(a); }
472 PointF normal() const { return isValid() ? PointF(a, b) : _directionInward; }
473 double signedDistance(PointI p) const { return normal() * p - c; }
474 PointF project(PointI p) const { return p - signedDistance(p) * normal(); }
475
476 void reverse() { std::reverse(_points.begin(), _points.end()); }
477
478 void add(PointI p) {
479 assert(_directionInward != PointF());
480 _points.push_back(p);
481 if (_points.size() == 1)
482 c = normal() * p;
483 }
484
485 void pop_back() { _points.pop_back(); }
486
487 void setDirectionInward(PointF d) { _directionInward = normalized(d); }
488
489 bool evaluate(double maxDist = -1)
490 {
491 auto ps = _points;
492 bool ret = evaluate(ps);
493 if (maxDist > 0) {
494 size_t old_points_size;
495 while (true) {
496 old_points_size = _points.size();
497 _points.erase(std::remove_if(_points.begin(), _points.end(),
498 [this, maxDist](PointI p) { return this->signedDistance(p) > maxDist; }),
499 _points.end());
500 if (old_points_size == _points.size())
501 break;
502#ifdef PRINT_DEBUG
503 printf("removed %zu points\n", old_points_size - _points.size());
504#endif
505 ret = evaluate(_points);
506 }
507 }
508 return ret;
509 }
510
511 double modules(PointF beg, PointF end) const
512 {
513 assert(_points.size() > 3);
514 std::vector<double> gapSizes;
515 gapSizes.reserve(_points.size());
516
517 // calculate the distance between the points projected onto the regression line
518 for (size_t i = 1; i < _points.size(); ++i)
519 gapSizes.push_back(distance(project(_points[i]), project(_points[i - 1])));
520
521 // calculate the (average) distance of two adjacent pixels
522 auto unitPixelDist = average(gapSizes, [](double dist){ return 0.75 < dist && dist < 1.5; });
523
524 // calculate the width of 2 modules (first black pixel to first black pixel)
525 double sum = distance(beg, project(_points.front())) - unitPixelDist;
526 auto i = gapSizes.begin();
527 for (auto dist : gapSizes) {
528 sum += dist;
529 if (dist > 1.9 * unitPixelDist) {
530 // c++14: *i++ = std::exchange(sum, 0.0);
531 *i++ = sum;
532 sum = 0.0;
533 }
534 }
535 *i++ = sum + distance(end, project(_points.back()));
536 gapSizes.erase(i, gapSizes.end());
537 auto lineLength = distance(beg, end) - unitPixelDist;
538 auto meanGapSize = lineLength / gapSizes.size();
539#ifdef PRINT_DEBUG
540 printf("unit pixel dist: %f\n", unitPixelDist);
541 printf("lineLength: %f, meanGapSize: %f, gaps: %lu\n", lineLength, meanGapSize, gapSizes.size());
542#endif
543 meanGapSize = average(gapSizes, [&](double dist){ return std::abs(dist - meanGapSize) < meanGapSize/2; });
544#ifdef PRINT_DEBUG
545 printf("lineLength: %f, meanGapSize: %f, gaps: %lu\n", lineLength, meanGapSize, gapSizes.size());
546#endif
547 return lineLength / meanGapSize;
548 }
549};
550
551PointF intersect(const RegressionLine& l1, const RegressionLine& l2)
552{
553 assert(l1.isValid() && l2.isValid());
554 double x, y, d;
555 d = l1.a * l2.b - l1.b * l2.a;
556 x = (l1.c * l2.b - l1.b * l2.c) / d;
557 y = (l1.a * l2.c - l1.c * l2.a) / d;
558 return {x, y};
559}
560
561class EdgeTracer
562{
563 const BitMatrix& image;
564 PointI p; // current position
565 PointF d; // current direction
566
567 static PointF mainDirection(PointF d)
568 {
569 assert(std::abs(d.x) != std::abs(d.y));
570 return std::abs(d.x) > std::abs(d.y) ? PointF(d.x, 0) : PointF(0, d.y);
571 }
572
573 enum class StepResult { FOUND, OPEN_END, CLOSED_END };
574
575 bool isIn(PointI p) const
576 {
577 const int b = 0;
578 return b <= p.x && p.x < image.width()-b &&
579 b <= p.y && p.y < image.height()-b;
580 }
581 bool isIn(PointF p) const { return isIn(round(p)); }
582 bool isIn() const { return isIn(p); }
583
584 class Value
585 {
586 enum { INVALID, WHITE, BLACK };
587 int v = INVALID;
588 public:
589 Value() = default;
590 Value(bool isBlack) : v(isBlack ? BLACK : WHITE) {}
591 bool isValid() const { return v != INVALID; }
592 bool isWhite() const { return v == WHITE; }
593 bool isBlack() const { return v == BLACK; }
594 };
595
596 Value getAt(PointF p) const
597 {
598 auto q = round(p);
599 if (!isIn(q))
600 return {};
601 return {image.get(q.x, q.y)};
602 }
603
604 bool blackAt(PointF p) const { return getAt(p).isBlack(); }
605 bool whiteAt(PointF p) const { return getAt(p).isWhite(); }
606 bool isEdge(PointF pos, PointF dir) const { return whiteAt(pos) && blackAt(pos + dir); }
607
608 StepResult traceStep(PointF dEdge, int maxStepSize, bool goodDirection)
609 {
610 dEdge = mainDirection(dEdge);
611 for (int breadth = 1; breadth <= (goodDirection ? 1 : (maxStepSize == 1 ? 2 : 3)); ++breadth)
612 for (int step = 1; step <= maxStepSize; ++step)
613 for (int i = 0; i <= 2*(step/4+1) * breadth; ++i) {
614 auto pEdge = p + step * d + (i&1 ? (i+1)/2 : -i/2) * dEdge;
615 log(round(pEdge));
616
617 if (!blackAt(pEdge + dEdge))
618 continue;
619
620 // found black pixel -> go 'outward' until we hit the b/w border
621 for (int j = 0; j < std::max(maxStepSize, 3) && isIn(pEdge); ++j) {
622 if (whiteAt(pEdge)) {
623 // if we are not making any progress, we still have another endless loop bug
624 assert(p != round(pEdge));
625 p = round(pEdge);
626 return StepResult::FOUND;
627 }
628 pEdge = pEdge - dEdge;
629 if (blackAt(pEdge - d))
630 pEdge = pEdge - d;
631 log(round(pEdge));
632 }
633 // no valid b/w border found within reasonable range
634 return StepResult::CLOSED_END;
635 }
636 return StepResult::OPEN_END;
637 }
638
639public:
640#ifdef PRINT_DEBUG
641 void log(const PointI& p) const
642 {
643 if (_log.height() != image.height() || _log.width() != image.width())
644 _log = LogBuffer(image.width(), image.height());
645 if (isIn(p))
646 _log.set(p.x, p.y, 1);
647 }
648#else
649 void log(const PointI&) const {}
650#endif
651
652 EdgeTracer(const BitMatrix& img, PointF p, PointF d) : image(img), p(p), d(d) {}
653 EdgeTracer& operator=(const EdgeTracer& other)
654 {
655 assert(&image == &other.image);
656 p = other.p;
657 d = other.d;
658 return *this;
659 }
660 EdgeTracer(const EdgeTracer&) = default;
661 ~EdgeTracer() = default;
662 EdgeTracer(EdgeTracer&&) noexcept(true) = default;
663 EdgeTracer& operator=(EdgeTracer&&) = default;
664
665 bool step(int s = 1)
666 {
667 p = round(p + s * d);
668 log(p);
669 return isIn(p);
670 }
671
672 void setDirection(PointF dir) { d = dir / std::max(std::abs(dir.x), std::abs(dir.y)); }
673
674 bool updateDirectionFromOrigin(PointF origin)
675 {
676 auto old_d = d;
677 setDirection(p - origin);
678 // if the new direction is pointing "backward", i.e. angle(new, old) > 90 deg -> break
679 if (d * old_d < 0)
680 return false;
681 // make sure d stays in the same quadrant to prevent an infinite loop
682 if (std::abs(d.x) == std::abs(d.y))
683 d = mainDirection(old_d) + 0.99 * (d - mainDirection(old_d));
684 else if (mainDirection(d) != mainDirection(old_d))
685 d = mainDirection(old_d) + 0.99 * mainDirection(d);
686 return true;
687 }
688
689 PointF front() const { return d; }
690 PointF back() const { return {-d.x, -d.y}; }
691 PointF right() const { return {-d.y, d.x}; }
692 PointF left() const { return {d.y, -d.x}; }
693
694 bool isEdgeBehind() const { return isEdge(PointF(p), back()); }
695
696 bool traceLine(PointF dEdge, RegressionLine& line)
697 {
698 line.setDirectionInward(dEdge);
699 do {
700 log(p);
701 line.add(p);
702 if (line.points().size() % 30 == 10) {
703 if (!line.evaluate())
704 return false;
705 if (!updateDirectionFromOrigin(p - line.project(p) + line.points().front()))
706 return false;
707 }
708 auto stepResult = traceStep(dEdge, 1, line.isValid());
709 if (stepResult != StepResult::FOUND)
710 return stepResult == StepResult::OPEN_END && line.points().size() > 1;
711 } while (true);
712 }
713
714 bool traceGaps(PointF dEdge, RegressionLine& line, int maxStepSize, const RegressionLine& finishLine)
715 {
716 line.setDirectionInward(dEdge);
717 int gaps = 0;
718 do {
719 assert(line.points().empty() || p != line.points().back());
720 log(p);
721
722 // if we drifted too far outside of the code, break
723 if (line.isValid() && line.signedDistance(p) < -5 && (!line.evaluate() || line.signedDistance(p) < -5))
724 return false;
725
726 // if we are drifting towards the inside of the code, pull the current position back out onto the line
727 if (line.isValid() && line.signedDistance(p) > 3) {
728 // The current direction d and the line we are tracing are supposed to be roughly parallel.
729 // In case the 'go outward' step in traceStep lead us astray, we might end up with a line
730 // that is almost perpendicular to d. Then the back-projection below can result in an
731 // endless loop. Break if the angle between d and line is greater than 45 deg.
732 if (std::abs(normalized(d) * line.normal()) > 0.7) // thresh is approx. sin(45 deg)
733 return false;
734
735 auto np = line.project(p);
736 // make sure we are making progress even when back-projecting:
737 // consider a 90deg corner, rotated 45deg. we step away perpendicular from the line and get
738 // back projected where we left off the line.
739 if (distance(np, line.project(line.points().back())) < 1)
740 np = np + d;
741 p = round(np);
742 }
743 else {
744 auto stepLengthInMainDir = line.points().empty() ? 0.0 : mainDirection(d) * (p - line.points().back());
745 line.add(p);
746
747 if (stepLengthInMainDir > 1) {
748 ++gaps;
749 if (gaps >= 2 || line.points().size() > 5) {
750 if (!line.evaluate(1.5))
751 return false;
752 if (!updateDirectionFromOrigin(p - line.project(p) + line.points().front()))
753 return false;
754 // check if the first half of the top-line trace is complete.
755 // the minimum code size is 10x10 -> every code has at least 4 gaps
756 //TODO: maybe switch to termination condition based on bottom line length to get a better
757 // finishLine for the right line trace
758 if (!finishLine.isValid() && gaps == 4) {
759 // undo the last insert, it will be inserted again after the restart
760 line.pop_back();
761 --gaps;
762 return true;
763 }
764 }
765 } else if (gaps == 0 && line.points().size() >= 2u * maxStepSize)
766 return false; // no point in following a line that has no gaps
767 }
768
769 if (finishLine.isValid())
770 maxStepSize = std::min(maxStepSize, static_cast<int>(finishLine.signedDistance(p)));
771
772 auto stepResult = traceStep(dEdge, maxStepSize, line.isValid());
773
774 if (stepResult != StepResult::FOUND)
775 // we are successful iff we found an open end across a valid finishLine
776 return stepResult == StepResult::OPEN_END && finishLine.isValid() &&
777 static_cast<int>(finishLine.signedDistance(p)) <= maxStepSize + 1;
778 } while (true);
779 }
780
781 bool traceCorner(PointF dir, PointF& corner)
782 {
783 step();
784 corner = PointF(p);
785 std::swap(d, dir);
786 traceStep(-1 * dir, 2, false);
787#ifdef PRINT_DEBUG
788 printf("turn: %d x %d -> %.2f, %.2f\n", p.x, p.y, d.x, d.y);
789#endif
790 return isIn(corner) && isIn(p);
791 }
792};

795
796static void log(const std::vector<PointI>& points, int color = 2)
797{
798 for (auto p : points)
799 _log.set(p.x, p.y, color);
800}
801
802static void dumpDebugPPM(const BitMatrix& image, const char* fn )
803{
804 FILE *f = fopen(fn, "wb");
805
806 // Write PPM header, P5 == grey, P6 == rgb
807 fprintf(f, "P6\n%d %d\n255\n", image.width(), image.height());
808
809 // Write pixels
810 for (int y = 0; y < image.height(); ++y)
811 for (int x = 0; x < image.width(); ++x) {
812 unsigned char r, g, b;
813 r = g = b = image.get(x, y) ? 0 : 255;
814 switch (_log.get(x, y)) {
815 case 1: r = g = b = r ? 230 : 50; break;
816 case 2: r = b = 50, g = 220; break;
817 case 3: g = r = 100, b = 250; break;
818 }
819 fwrite(&r, 1, 1, f);
820 fwrite(&g, 1, 1, f);
821 fwrite(&b, 1, 1, f);
822 }
823 fclose(f);
824}
825#endif

827static DetectorResult SampleGrid(const BitMatrix& image, PointF tl, PointF bl, PointF br, PointF tr, int width, int height)
828{
829 auto moveTowardsBy = [](PointF& a, const PointF& b, double d) {
830 auto a2b = normalized(b - a);
831 a = a + d * a2b;
832 };
833
834 // shrink shape by half a pixel to go from center of white pixel outside of code to the edge between white and black
835 moveTowardsBy(tl, br, 0.5);
836 moveTowardsBy(br, tl, 0.5);
837 moveTowardsBy(bl, tr, 0.5);
838 // move the tr point a little less because the jagged top and right line tend to be statistically slightly
839 // inclined toward the center anyway.
840 moveTowardsBy(tr, bl, 0.3);
841
842 // work around a missing 'round' in GridSampler.
843 // TODO: the correct location for the rounding is after the transformation in GridSampler
844 // but that would currently break other 2D encoders
845 for (auto* p : {&tl, &bl, &br, &tr})
846 *p = *p + PointF(0.5, 0.5);
847
848 return SampleGrid(image, width, height, PerspectiveTransform(Rectangle(width, height, 0), {tl, tr, br, bl}));
849}
850
851static DetectorResult DetectNew(const BitMatrix& image, bool tryRotate)
852{
853 // walk to the left at first
854 for (auto startDirection : {PointF(-1, 0), PointF(1, 0), PointF(0, -1), PointF(0, 1)}) {
855 EdgeTracer startTracer(image, PointF(image.width()/2, image.height()/2), startDirection);
856 while (startTracer.step()) {
857 // go forward until we reach a white/black border
858 if (!startTracer.isEdgeBehind())
859 continue;
860
861#ifdef PRINT_DEBUG
862#define continue { \
863 printf("broke at %d\n", __LINE__); \
864 for (auto* l : {&lineL, &lineB, &lineT, &lineR}) log(l->points()); \
865 continue; \
866 }
867#endif
868
869 PointF tl, bl, br, tr;
870 RegressionLine lineL, lineB, lineR, lineT;
871
872 auto t = startTracer;
873
874 // follow left leg upwards
875 t.setDirection(t.right());
876 if (!t.traceLine(t.right(), lineL))
877 continue;
878
879 if (!t.traceCorner(t.right(), tl))
880 continue;
881 lineL.reverse();
882 auto tlTracer = t;
883
884 // follow left leg downwards
885 t = startTracer;
886 t.setDirection(tlTracer.right());
887 if (!t.traceLine(t.left(), lineL))
888 continue;
889
890 if (!lineL.isValid())
891 t.updateDirectionFromOrigin(tl);
892 auto up = t.back();
893 if (!t.traceCorner(t.left(), bl))
894 continue;
895
896 // follow bottom leg right
897 if (!t.traceLine(t.left(), lineB))
898 continue;
899
900 if (!lineB.isValid())
901 t.updateDirectionFromOrigin(bl);
902 auto right = t.front();
903 if (!t.traceCorner(t.left(), br))
904 continue;
905
906 auto lenL = distance(tl, bl) - 1;
907 auto lenB = distance(bl, br) - 1;
908 if (lenL < 10 || lenB < 10 || lenB < lenL / 4 || lenB > lenL * 8)
909 continue;
910
911 auto maxStepSize = static_cast<int>(lenB / 5 + 1); // datamatrix dim is at least 10x10
912
913 // at this point we found a plausible L-shape and are now looking for the b/w pattern at the top and right:
914 // follow top row right 'half way' (4 gaps), see traceGaps break condition with 'invalid' line
915 tlTracer.setDirection(right);
916 if (!tlTracer.traceGaps(tlTracer.right(), lineT, maxStepSize, RegressionLine()))
917 continue;
918
919 maxStepSize = std::min(lineT.length() / 3, static_cast<int>(lenL / 5)) * 2;
920
921 // follow up until we reach the top line
922 t.setDirection(up);
923 if (!t.traceGaps(t.left(), lineR, maxStepSize, lineT))
924 continue;
925
926 if (!t.traceCorner(t.left(), tr))
927 continue;
928
929 auto lenT = distance(tl, tr) - 1;
930 auto lenR = distance(tr, br) - 1;
931
932 if (std::abs(lenT - lenB) / lenB > 0.5 || std::abs(lenR - lenL) / lenL > 0.5 ||
933 lineT.points().size() < 5 || lineR.points().size() < 5)
934 continue;
935
936 // continue top row right until we cross the right line
937 if (!tlTracer.traceGaps(tlTracer.right(), lineT, maxStepSize, lineR))
938 continue;
939
940#ifdef PRINT_DEBUG
941 printf("L: %f, %f ^ %f, %f > %f, %f (%d : %d : %d : %d)\n", bl.x, bl.y,
942 tl.x - bl.x, tl.y - bl.y, br.x - bl.x, br.y - bl.y, (int)lenL, (int)lenB, (int)lenT, (int)lenR);
943#endif
944
945 for (RegressionLine* l : {&lineL, &lineB, &lineT, &lineR})
946 l->evaluate(1.0);
947
948 // find the bounding box corners of the code with sub-pixel precision by intersecting the 4 border lines
949 bl = intersect(lineB, lineL);
950 tl = intersect(lineT, lineL);
951 tr = intersect(lineT, lineR);
952 br = intersect(lineB, lineR);
953
954 int dimT, dimR;
955 double fracT, fracR;
956 auto splitDouble = [](double d, int* i, double* f) {
957 *i = std::isnormal(d) ? static_cast<int>(d + 0.5) : 0;
958 *f = std::isnormal(d) ? std::abs(d - *i) : INFINITY;
959 };
960 splitDouble(lineT.modules(tl, tr), &dimT, &fracT);
961 splitDouble(lineR.modules(br, tr), &dimR, &fracR);
962
963#ifdef PRINT_DEBUG
964 printf("L: %f, %f ^ %f, %f > %f, %f ^> %f, %f\n", bl.x, bl.y,
965 tl.x - bl.x, tl.y - bl.y, br.x - bl.x, br.y - bl.y, tr.x, tr.y);
966 printf("dim: %d x %d\n", dimT, dimR);
967#endif
968
969 // if we have an invalid rectangular data matrix dimension, we try to parse it by assuming a square
970 // we use the dimension that is closer to an integral value
971 if (dimT < 2 * dimR || dimT > 4 * dimR)
972 dimT = dimR = fracR < fracT ? dimR : dimT;
973
974 // the dimension is 2x the number of black/white transitions
975 dimT *= 2;
976 dimR *= 2;
977
978 if (dimT < 10 || dimT > 144 || dimR < 8 || dimR > 144 )
979 continue;
980
981 auto res = SampleGrid(image, tl, bl, br, tr, dimT, dimR);
982
983#ifdef PRINT_DEBUG
984 printf("modules top: %d, right: %d\n", dimT, dimR);
985 printf("%s", ToString(bits).c_str());
986
987 for (RegressionLine* l : {&lineL, &lineB, &lineT, &lineR})
988 log(l->points());
989
990 dumpDebugPPM(image, "binary.pnm");
991#endif
992
993 if (!res.isValid())
994 continue;
995
996 return res;
997 }
998 // reached border of image -> try next scan direction
999#ifndef PRINT_DEBUG
1000 if (!tryRotate)
1001#endif
1002 break; // only test left direction
1003 }
1004
1005#ifdef PRINT_DEBUG
1006 dumpDebugPPM(image, "binary.pnm");
1007#endif
1008
1009 return {};
1010}
1011
1012/**
1013* This method detects a code in a "pure" image -- that is, pure monochrome image
1014* which contains only an unrotated, unskewed, image of a code, with some white border
1015* around it. This is a specialized method that works exceptionally fast in this special
1016* case.
1017*/
1018static DetectorResult DetectPure(const BitMatrix& image)
1019{
1020 const int minSize = 8; // datamatrix codes are at least 8x8 modules
1021 int left, top, width, height;
1022 if (!image.findBoundingBox(left, top, width, height, minSize)) {
1023 return {};
1024 }
1025
1026 // find the first white pixel on the diagonal
1027 int moduleSize = 1;
1028 while (moduleSize < width / minSize && image.get(left + moduleSize, top))
1029 ++moduleSize;
1030
1031 int matrixWidth = width / moduleSize;
1032 int matrixHeight = height / moduleSize;
1033 if (matrixWidth < minSize || matrixHeight < minSize) {
1034 return {};
1035 }
1036
1037 // Push in the "border" by half the module width so that we start
1038 // sampling in the middle of the module. Just in case the image is a
1039 // little off, this will help recover.
1040 int msh = moduleSize / 2;
1041 int right = left + width - 1;
1042 int bottom = top + height - 1;
1043
1044 // Now just read off the bits (this is a crop + subsample)
1045 return {Deflate(image, matrixWidth, matrixHeight, top + msh, left + msh, moduleSize),
1046 {{left, top}, {right, top}, {right, bottom}, {left, bottom}}};
1047}
1048
1049DetectorResult Detector::Detect(const BitMatrix& image, bool tryHarder, bool tryRotate, bool isPure)
1050{
1051 if (isPure)
1052 return DetectPure(image);
1053
1054 auto result = DetectNew(image, tryRotate);
1055 if (!result.isValid() && tryHarder)
1056 result = DetectOld(image);
1057 return result;
1058}
